    "created_at": "2024-06-28T20:13:42Z",
    "updated_at": "2024-06-28T20:13:42Z",
    "body": "I had the same issue (Bash opening in POSIX mode / the default shell did not change/ some other weird behaviours) and for me it turned out that kitty did not have \"full disk access\" (which can be enabled in the settings) -- There was no warning or anything in that regard but changing this fixed everything for me",
    "author_association": "NONE",
